description: From Late Latin irrefūtābilis, from in- (“not”) +‎ refūtābilis (“refutable”), from refūtō, refūtāre (“to refute”) +‎ -bilis (“-able”).

adjectives.description: irrefutable (comparative more irrefutable, superlative most irrefutable)

entries.meaning: undeniable; unable to be disproved or refuted
